<br>
In order to increase Fletching, I must have skills in Metalworking, Clothmaking and Woodworking.<br>
<br>
When I increase in Fletching it does not necessarily increase enough in these other items.  Bows cost alot to make as they take 24 boards or more to make something.  Arrows don't increase clothmaking, so you must do both.  And metalworking is arrows or staffs.<br>
<br>
It seems I spend all my time on the other things and rarely get to increase fletching.  It's become costly to do this.  Yes I do the consignments but then I hit a point where I need to increase in one of the other skills.<br>
<br>
Is it suppose to be this way?<br>
Are there any hints out there that you can give me?<br>
Does anyone know of anywhere that there is half-decent fletching info?<br>
<br>
I am just so frustrated I spent two hours this monring and raised my fletching skill 28 points because I had to spend time increasing the others.  <br>
<br>
&lt;sigh&gt;<br>
